{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κατα-τρίβω</b> [ῑ], <br /> <i>future</i> -ψω [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Cyr.” 8.4.36 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> - [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" τέτρῐφα Isocrates Orator [{5-6th c.BC}] \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>] (see. below):—<i>passive</i>, <i>future</i> -[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" τρῐβήσομαι Xenophon Historicus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 5.4.60 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]:— <b>rub down</b> or <b>away</b>: hence, <br /><Level3><b>__1</b></Level3> of clothes, <b>wear out</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" ἀμφὶ πλευρῇσι δοράς 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 55, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “fragment” 345, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phd.” 87c, 4th c.AD: Metrodorus Epigrammaticus “fragment” 55: hence _metaphorically_, πολλὰ σώματα κατατρίψασα ἡ ψυχή Plato Philosophus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Phaedo” 91d, compare 87d; οἱ τὰ βήματα κατατετριφότες\">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>], i.e. <b>constant frequenters</b> of the tribune, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator “Ep.” 8.7; ὁ σταλαγμὸς κ. 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Physica” 253b15 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>metaphorically</i>, κ. τὸ τῆς ἀρετῆς ὄνομα <b>to have</b> it <b>always on one's tongue</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Par.” 43. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__1.b</b></Level4> <b>press downwards</b>, -[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" ομένης πάτῳ τῆς ῥίζης Theophrastus Philosophus [{4-3rd c.BC}] “Historia Plantarum” 6.6.10 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]. <br /><Level4><b>__1.c</b></Level4> <b>rub</b> or <b>roll</b> thread, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" περὶ γούνατι νῆμα χειρί 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 24.77 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]. <br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> of persons, <b>wear out, exhaust</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" αὐτοὺς περὶ ἑαυτοὺς τοὺς Ἕλληνας κ. 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 8.46 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <b>to be quite worn out</b>, with <i>participle</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" κατατετρίμμεθα πλανώμενοι Aristophanes Comicus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Pax” 355, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Mem.” 1.2.37; - τριβήσοιντο ὑπὸ πολέμου [prev\\. author] “HG” 5.4.60; ἐν τοῖς στρατοπέδοις Isocrates Orator [{5-6th c.BC}] 15.115; περὶ τὸν πόλεμον Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus [{1-2nd c.AD}] “Fabius Maximus” 19 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]. <br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> of Time, <b>spend, consume</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" κατέτριψε τὴν ἡμέραν δημηγορῶν 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 57.9, compare 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 2.14, 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Epit.” 54, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Caes.” 13; τὰς ἡμέρας περὶ τῶν τυχόντων 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Nicomachea” 1117b35, compare 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 5.62.6, etc.; κ. τὸν βίον\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] <b>employ</b> it <b>fully</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Mem.” 4.7.5, 4th c.BC(?): Nicolaus Comicus 1.23, compare 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Rh.” 1.38 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus:\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —so in <i>middle</i>, τὸ πολὺ τοῦ βίου ἐν δικαστηρίοις φεύγων τε καὶ διώκων κ. <b>waste</b> the greater part of one's life in.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “R.” 405b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: in <i>perfect</i> <i>passive</i> (later in <i>aorist 2</i> -[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" τρῐβέντες “Codex Just.” 1.5.16.5)\">Refs</a>], <b>wear away one's life, pass one's whole time</b>, with <i>participle</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" αὐλοῖς καὶ λύραισι κατατέτριμμαι χρώμενος Aristophanes Comicus [{5-6th c.BC}] “fragment” 221; κ. στρατευόμενος Xenophon Historicus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Memorabilia” 3.4.1; ἐπί τινι 4th c.AD: Themistius Sophista “Orationes” 26.312c \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]. <br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> of property, etc., <b>squander</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" ἅπαντα Xenophon Historicus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 8.4.36; τὸν λόγον περί τι 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis “Comp.” 11 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>].","strongNumber":"G7939","accentedUnicode":"κατατρίβω","shortDef":"to wear away","mediumDef":"to wear away","stepGloss":"to wear away","stepTransliteration":"katatribō","count":0,"_step_Type":"verb"}]}